The country remains on level 3 lockdown despite approaching the coronavirus peak. However stricter regulations have been put in place to battle the spread of Covid-19. The sale, dispensing and distribution of alcohol has been suspended and an evening curfew has been implemented. Ministers from the social cluster are giving an update on the amended lockdown regulations. JOHANNESBURG - The National Coronavirus Command Council will continue to brief the country on Monday following President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address to the nation on Sunday. The social cluster will hold a briefing on government's plans to combat the spread of COVID-19 in South Africa. WATCH: NCCC updates SA on amended regulations Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize will lead the briefing. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.